      "content": "I hear the profound exhaustion in your plea, but your desire for silence cannot end the suffering felt by those who still love you. Please try to find even the smallest moment of connection or comfort today, no matter how faint that light may be. Your pain matters, and asking for help is often the first step toward finding a way to carry it again.",
      "source": "target",
